Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.55,0:02:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] Where do you\Nthink they're taking us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.64,0:02:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm gonna go with jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.97,0:02:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- I still can't believe that fishing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.55,0:02:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pole guy took us out like it was nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Welcome to Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were Ironwood's Ace Operatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.85,0:02:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.89,0:02:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys had a run-in with the Ace-Ops?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.22,0:02:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ironwood must really have\Na bone to pick with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] They're not that big of a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.72,0:02:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not that big of a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.64,0:02:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ace-Ops are the\Nelite-of-elite military huntsmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.39,0:02:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Ironwood's personal attack dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.22,0:02:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- So they got you too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Pfft!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.47,0:02:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't let myself get caught by them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here because I've been speaking out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,against Atlas' exploitation of Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And General Ironwood is\Ntrying to silence me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.43,0:02:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Guard-Driver] You\Nthrew a brick at her ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.05,0:03:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's worth it if it gets\Npeople talking about our cause!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.14,0:03:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Our cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.43,0:03:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, the fight for better\Nconditions in Mantle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.68,0:03:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead by the charismatic, talented,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,lovely, Robyn Hill and\Nher Happy Huntresses!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all top Atlas Academy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.51,0:03:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,graduates, who could've\Nsigned up for the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.30,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But Robyn and the Huntresses\Nchose to stay in Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gunning for a seat\Non the kingdom's council,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.76,0:03:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and when she gets it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.22,0:03:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,she's gonna put an end\Nto Ironwood's tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] Happy Huntresses?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is that their real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't you think tyranny's\Na little dramatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Easy to say for a Schnee heiress
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,living comfortably up in Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.18,0:03:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.35,0:03:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Whoa, it's gorgeous up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.22,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't let that fool you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- This isn't the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.55,0:04:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Atlas Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.22,0:04:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- I guess we will be seeing the General.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.22,0:04:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For better or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.76,0:04:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ren] So what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] I don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.05,0:04:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should be careful with what we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.97,0:05:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- We'll follow your lead, Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.68,0:05:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ironwood] I swear if\NI have to sit through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,one more council meeting like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.60,0:05:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yay, you're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.80,0:05:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Anyone wanna give us a hand with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.01,0:05:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- You have 10 seconds to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.55,0:05:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,take those off, before\NI start hurting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.47,0:05:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Both Guards] Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sorry!\N- Please let us help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.22,0:05:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Guard] Forgive us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.39,0:05:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so good to see all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.80,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Our reception didn't really convey that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.26,0:06:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- I sincerely regret how\Nyou were treated by my team.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.01,0:06:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When a rouge airship\Nentered our airspace,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.10,0:06:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it raised some red flags.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.47,0:06:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We assumed the ship was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.26,0:06:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay yeah, it was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.43,0:06:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- You stole an Atlas airship?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You might've been shot down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How unbelievably irresponsi--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry I worried you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.47,0:06:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But we did what we had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.47,0:06:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.97,0:06:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I cannot believe that you\Nallowed this to happen, Qrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.64,0:06:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- You try stoppin' these kids\Nwhen they have their mind
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.85,0:06:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,set on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We have some important information
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:06:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for you that's... confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, is it about the Relics?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.43,0:07:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Or perhaps the Winter Maiden?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.39,0:07:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- You told them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.72,0:07:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.26,0:07:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really think
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you were the only one who got to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.55,0:07:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,work on a new plan after Beacon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,With Ozpin gone I needed my own
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,team of people I could trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.22,0:07:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, I told them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.68,0:07:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ace-Ops too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.97,0:07:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why I'm so glad\Nyou're here with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, I believed it was impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.85,0:07:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to truly turn the tide against Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.22,0:07:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oz has pushed her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Has kept victory out of her claws
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.10,0:07:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but she will keep returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.35,0:07:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Stronger and stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.93,0:07:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless we destroy her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.97,0:07:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- But, what about the Atlas Relic?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- You mean the Staff of Creation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.05,0:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's safe inside the Vault!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.89,0:08:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Qrow] And the Winter Maiden?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.05,0:08:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- She is secure and in stable condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.18,0:08:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stable condition, what does tha--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.72,0:08:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- She's uh, not exactly a spring chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.01,0:08:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know how this all looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Recalling my military?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The embargo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably don't seem the\Nmost trustworthy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then why continue it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.72,0:08:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- The people of Mantle are hurting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- I needed to ensure
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.39,0:08:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem couldn't infiltrate Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.55,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted my military here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Protecting my people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.93,0:08:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- But it's not protecting them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.18,0:08:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's making everyone hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's a price I'm willing to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.47,0:08:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you all have been\Nentrusted with the knowledge of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you all to trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.89,0:08:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozpin believed the best way to fight Salem
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.47,0:08:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was to do so in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.89,0:08:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether that was the right choice or not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't for me to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.22,0:09:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But we find ourselves in\Nthe position of needing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.80,0:09:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,well, a new approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- And what do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.89,0:09:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's Amity Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.68,0:09:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where the Vytal Festival is held?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.55,0:09:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Indeed. When Beacon fell
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.80,0:09:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone on Remnant lost\Ncontact with one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew our current system was outdated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.97,0:09:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Amity was built to bring\Nthe nations together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.80,0:09:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will serve that purpose once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.85,0:09:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Penny] Isn't it great?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not going to just\Nreplace Beacon Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.47,0:09:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Building a new tower on top of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.26,0:09:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Amity Colosseum will re-establish\Nglobal communications!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- By launching the tower\Nhigh into the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.43,0:09:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our scientists believe\Nwe can create a sort-of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.05,0:09:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,satellite -- out of reach of the Grimm,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.64,0:09:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and capable of maintaining global
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.30,0:09:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,communications even if we\Nwere to lose another tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- That is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- James, you don't need the\Nentire military for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.10,0:10:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will for the next part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.01,0:10:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I finally tell\Nthe people about Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh, so that's why you\Nwithdrew your troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle the panic that\Nwill break out in Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, panic is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And panic brings Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I believe we are ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.18,0:10:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once Atlas has come to\Ngrips with the fight ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll use Amity Tower to spread the message
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.47,0:10:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of Remnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.47,0:10:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- But everything will fall apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Grimm will be everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.97,0:10:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're right, but Atlas is\Nwilling and prepared to assist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.05,0:10:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Trying to hide the truth from the world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.93,0:10:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,will eventually kill us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.18,0:11:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oz spent his whole life, many\Nlives, keeping this secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.60,0:11:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know. But since\NBeacon, things have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.51,0:11:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Without him here to guide us,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.80,0:11:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all I can do is use my best judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.93,0:11:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.30,0:11:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Actually, Oz isn't completely gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh, Oscar here is... is the next Ozpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.39,0:11:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oz?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.93,0:11:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so glad you're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think you --
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.01,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not quite. He's kind of,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.26,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,um, gone at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he --\N- We don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in a train crash,\Nand ever since, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly Oz wasn't there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:11:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's the worst news yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.35,0:12:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you learn anything from\Nhim about the Relics before?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.55,0:12:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- He told us the lamp can\Nanswer three questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But, all the questions\Nwere used up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.01,0:12:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.47,0:12:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozpin told us that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At least we have you Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.10,0:12:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safe here in Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe together we can figure\Nout how to bring Ozpin back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thank you, sir... I mean, uh, General...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.97,0:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Ironwood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.72,0:12:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're giving it back to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.47,0:12:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- After what happened with the Ace-Ops,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.55,0:12:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to think I'm\Nkeeping anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:12:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially something as important as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, I think it's safest
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.01,0:13:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with the people who brought it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Um... thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- We must work together if\Nwe're to fight Salem and win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.85,0:13:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're all on board...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.89,0:13:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tell us how we can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good, because getting the\NAmity Tower ready to launch
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.93,0:13:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.64,0:13:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But first,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.64,0:13:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we need to get\Nthose weapons of yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.18,0:13:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,up to our standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Remember, this is Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,While assisting the military,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we will provide you\Nwith the best equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.22,0:13:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,our scientists can devise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Everyone] Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- So that was the second\Ntime I got banned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.60,0:13:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was the third time when --
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- All right, cut the chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.51,0:14:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'd like to sincerely apologize
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.55,0:14:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the miscommunication down in Mantle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.60,0:14:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't intend to --
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.55,0:14:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- I feel so bad, honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.05,0:14:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had known who you were we'd be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,laughing over a hot meal right now and--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.64,0:14:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- I understand, you were\Njust following orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- I mean you could have asked\Nus some questions first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Questions are for the weak, but we're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.43,0:14:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all on the same team now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.97,0:14:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that I'm happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.89,0:14:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- We just wanted to say we're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that we're looking forward
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to working with you on our next mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be students, but you've
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,been fighting just as hard as we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.01,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Exactly why I'm\Nlooking forward to seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.68,0:14:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what you kids can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ugh, not everything's\Na competition Hare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- C'mon, let me show you around campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.72,0:14:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Qrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.22,0:15:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I meant it when I said it\Nwas good to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.05,0:15:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh, yeah, you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- So that way's the cafeteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that way is the training rooms, oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.51,0:15:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and over there are the classrooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.47,0:15:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- This all looks great, Penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.05,0:15:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But where are we staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.93,0:15:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Remember, you're in Atlas now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.26,0:15:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As the most well-funded school on Remnant,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.68,0:15:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,every teen at Atlas Academy gets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.30,0:15:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their own room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.76,0:15:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that wasn't enough --
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- So we're staying in the dorms?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.72,0:15:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- It'll be just like Beacon again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.97,0:16:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Intercom] The kingdom\Nof Atlas will remain strong
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.22,0:16:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will remain safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.43,0:16:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That is my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- For the last time, a singular hideout
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.55,0:16:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,makes us more susceptible to discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.72,0:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Tyrian] But what if we're seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.43,0:16:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we're recognized?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- We stay mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Tyrian] We're walking\Naround a city with
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.72,0:16:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- While cyber security has\Nbeen stepped up in Atlas,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as usual, none of the code\Nwas updated in Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.64,0:16:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Tyrian] That certainly sounds useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.14,0:16:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- It should be, I helped\Nwrite that code after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.43,0:17:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah, well, I suppose we\Nall have our talents.
